motif_definitions.M1_pure_sensor: Only sensor-to-motor synapses active (w03-w24). No cross-wiring, no self-feedback. The feedforward archetype.
motif_definitions.M2_sensor_cross: Sensor-to-motor plus motor-to-motor cross-wiring (w34/w43). No self-feedback. Motors coordinate laterally.
motif_definitions.M3_sensor_self: Sensor-to-motor plus self-feedback (w33/w44). No cross-wiring. Each motor has memory but no lateral coordination.
motif_definitions.M4_full_network: All three synapse classes active: sensor-to-motor, cross-wiring, and self-feedback. Maximum recurrence.
motif_definitions.M5_minimal: Four or fewer active synapses. Sparse network — maximum function from minimum structure.
motif_definitions.M6_maximal: All 10 possible synapses active in standard topology. Dense network.
motif_definitions.M7_hidden_layer: Network includes hidden neurons between sensors and motors. Adds computational depth — signals are processed before reaching motors.
motif_definitions.F1_no_feedback: No self-feedback (w33=0, w44=0). Pure feedforward dynamics.
motif_definitions.F2_standard_feedback: Standard self-feedback: w33>0 (back leg positive), w44<0 (front leg negative). The canonical oscillator-amplifier pattern.
motif_definitions.F3_reversed_feedback: Reversed self-feedback: w33<0, w44>0. Inverted proprioception — destabilizing.
motif_definitions.F4_same_sign_feedback: Both self-feedbacks share the same sign. Sustaining rather than alternating.
motif_definitions.F5_hidden_oscillator: Oscillation generated by hidden neuron cross-inhibition rather than motor self-feedback. A central pattern generator.

skill_definitions.S1_strider: High displacement (>15), mostly straight (>0.65), stable. The efficient long-distance walker.
skill_definitions.S2_sprinter: Very high displacement (>25). Raw speed regardless of path quality.
skill_definitions.S3_drifter: Moderate displacement (5-15), curved path (<0.5 straightness). Goes somewhere, but indirectly.
skill_definitions.S4_spinner: High path length relative to displacement (straightness < 0.15). Walking in circles.
skill_definitions.S5_statue: Near-static displacement (<2). Moves limbs but stays in place.
skill_definitions.S6_faller: Height collapses below 50% of initial. The robot falls over during simulation.
skill_definitions.S7_bouncer: Large vertical oscillation (z_range > 0.6). Bouncy gait with significant height variation.
skill_definitions.S8_glider: Smooth vertical profile (z_range < 0.2), stable. Floats rather than bounces.
skill_definitions.S9_crab: Lateral displacement dominates forward (|DY/DX| > 1.5). Walking sideways.
skill_definitions.T1_metronome: Highly periodic joints (ACF peak > 0.3). Clock-like regularity.
skill_definitions.T2_chaotic: No detectable periodicity in joint signals. Aperiodic motion.
skill_definitions.T3_never_settler: Gait never reaches steady state within simulation (transient > 3000 steps).
skill_definitions.C1_anti_phase: Legs alternate in anti-phase (phase fraction 0.35-0.65). The canonical walking gait.
skill_definitions.C2_in_phase: Legs move together in-phase (phase fraction <0.15 or >0.85). Hopping or bounding.
skill_definitions.C3_asymmetric_amplitude: One joint has >2x the amplitude of the other. Unilateral drive.
skill_definitions.E1_efficient: Top-quartile efficiency (displacement per unit energy). Does more with less.
skill_definitions.E2_turner: Significant yaw accumulation (>1.0 rad total). The robot rotates during locomotion.
skill_definitions.E3_backward: Walks backward (dx < -0.5). Negative displacement on the X axis.
